<ixml
  ><comment> Sample grammar 3

from https://homepages.cwi.nl/~steven/Talks/2013/08-07-invisible-xml/invisible-xml-3.html
</comment
  ><comment> Revisions:
2018-04-08 : CMSMcQ : made this from sample.grammar.03.xml
</comment
  ><rule name="css"
    ><alt
      ><nonterminal name="rules"
    /></alt
  ></rule
  ><rule name="rules"
    ><alt
      ><nonterminal name="rule"
    /></alt
    ><alt
      ><nonterminal name="rules"
      /><nonterminal name="rule"
    /></alt
  ></rule
  ><rule name="rule"
    ><alt
      ><nonterminal name="selector"
      /><nonterminal name="block"
    /></alt
  ></rule
  ><rule name="block"
    ><alt
      ><literal string="{"
      /><nonterminal name="properties"
      /><literal string="}"
    /></alt
  ></rule
  ><rule name="properties"
    ><alt
      ><nonterminal name="property"
    /></alt
    ><alt
      ><nonterminal name="property"
      /><literal string=";"
      /><nonterminal name="properties"
    /></alt
  ></rule
  ><rule name="property"
    ><alt
      ><nonterminal name="name"
      /><literal string=":"
      /><nonterminal name="value"
    /></alt
    ><alt
      ><nonterminal name="empty"
    /></alt
  ></rule
  ><rule name="selector"
    ><alt
      ><nonterminal name="name"
    /></alt
  ></rule
  ><rule name="name"
    ><alt
      ><inclusion
        ><range from="a" to="z"
        /><range from="A" to="Z"
      /></inclusion
      ><repeat0
        ><inclusion
          ><range from="a" to="z"
          /><range from="A" to="Z"
          /><range from="0" to="9"
          /><literal string="-"
          /><literal string="_"
        /></inclusion
      ></repeat0
    ></alt
  ></rule
  ><rule name="value"
    ><alt
      ><inclusion
        ><range from="x" to="z"
      /></inclusion
    ></alt
  ></rule
  ><comment> An earlier form of grammar 3 didn't actually define
the nonterminal 'empty'.  That might be related to the
exponential problem. </comment
  ><rule name="empty"
    ><alt
  /></rule
></ixml>
